-- Draghi Says Stress Tests Will Show Italian Banks Have `Adequate' Capital
-- Flavia Krause-Jackson
-- 2010-07-15T08:53:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/draghi-says-stress-tests-will-show-italian-banks-have-adequate-capital.html

          
          
             Bank of Italy Governor Mario Draghi
said he is confident that European Union stress tests will show
that the country’s lenders have “adequate” capital and fulfill
criteria above the minimum required.  
 He spoke today in a speech delivered at the Italian
Bankers’ Association in Rome.  
          
          


  


        